==Scottish==

===Etymology===
The root of which is [[Irish Gaelic]] ''doire'', '[[oak]] wood; dweller by the oak wood' or 'attendant of the oak grove', since the oak was sacred in [[Celtic]] lore, tended by the [[druid]]s.

===Proper noun===
'''Adair'''

